CatDescriptText: Delsey McKay was the stage name of Marion E. (Tabb) Brown, a pianist and songwriter who performed on the bills with such greats as Duke Ellington and Aretha Franklin.  She achieved international fame after winning a popular music festival in Belgium and touring Europe.
